<item>
            <title>[SOLR-17494] Remove client language specific wt formats</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-17494</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Community survey suggests folks don&apos;t use wt=ruby, wt=php, wt=python writer types.&#160;&#160; Another sign of that is the Choosing an Output Format page in the Ref Doc has a broken link to xref:query-guide:response-writers.adoc.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://solr.apache.org/guide/solr/latest/deployment-guide/client-apis.html#choosing-an-output-format&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://solr.apache.org/guide/solr/latest/deployment-guide/client-apis.html#choosing-an-output-format&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is to explore the impact of removing the language specific writer types.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
